## PRIORITY 3: RISK ZONE (Week 2)

### P3.1 - Export Pattern Standardization [RISK: delta_s=0.65]
**Goal**: Unified export pattern across all 45 packages
**Standard**:
```javascript
// src/index.js - Direct exports + package.json exports field
export { ClassA, ClassB } from './class-a.js';
export { UtilityFn } from './utility.js';
export * as namespaced from './module.js'; // Only if logically grouped
```

**Tasks**:
- [x] Phase 1: Audit all 44 packages (COMPLETE - Dec 1, 2025)
  - [x] 44 local @sequential/* packages audited
  - [x] Top 10 most-imported dependencies analyzed
  - [x] Export patterns classified (Direct/Wildcard/CJS/None)
  - [x] Exports field detection completed
- [ ] Phase 2: Critical Fixes (5 packages, 2.5 hours)
  - [ ] sequential-machine: Add ESM wrapper (30 min)
  - [ ] sequential-runner: Create src/index.js (45 min)
  - [ ] chat-component: Fix exports field or create index (30 min)
  - [ ] sequential-wrapped-services: Audit exports (30 min)
  - [ ] sequential-wrapper: Audit exports (30 min)
- [ ] Phase 3: Low Priority Fixes (5 packages, 1 hour)
  - [ ] Add exports fields: desktop-api-client, desktop-ui-components, zellous-client-sdk (30 min)
  - [ ] Optional ESM wrappers: sequential-fetch, sequential-flow (30 min)
- [ ] Phase 4: Validation (30 min)
  - [ ] Run import tests across all packages
  - [ ] Verify exports fields resolve correctly
  - [ ] Check for circular dependencies
**Owner**: Claude (audit complete) + parallel agents for Phase 2-3 fixes
**Time Est**: 4 hours total (audit: 1h ✅ | fixes: 3h | validation: 0.5h)
**Impact**: Consistency, easier maintenance, better tree-shaking

