### Standard Pattern Template

For all new packages and refactoring:

```javascript
// src/index.js
export { ClassA, ClassB } from './class-a.js';
export { UtilityFn } from './utility.js';
export { ERROR_CODES, createError } from './errors.js';
```

```json
// package.json
{
  "name": "@sequential/package-name",
  "type": "module",
  "main": "src/index.js",
  "exports": {
    ".": "./src/index.js"
  }
}
```

**Benefits**:
- Explicit API surface
- Tree-shakeable
- Clear import paths
- IDE autocomplete
- TypeScript-friendly
- Zero ambiguity

