### 2. zellous Assessment

#### What It Is

**Real-Time Collaboration Library**:
- **Description**: WebRTC-based real-time collaboration with PTT, rooms, file sharing
- **Purpose**: Enable collaborative features in desktop apps
- **Origin**: AnEntrypoint project (https://github.com/AnEntrypoint/zellous.git)
- **Version**: 2.0.0
- **Type**: Node.js library with WebSocket server + browser SDK

**Architecture**:
```
zellous/                          # Server package (23MB)
├── lib/zellous-core.js          # Core collaboration logic
├── lib/default-handlers.js      # Message handlers
├── server.js                    # Express + WebSocket server
└── osjs/                        # OS.js integration (legacy)

zellous-client-sdk/              # Client SDK (40KB)
├── zellous-sdk.js               # Browser WebSocket client
└── index.js                     # ESM exports
```

#### Size & Complexity

**Lightweight**:
- **zellous server**: 23MB (148,653 lines)
- **zellous-client-sdk**: 40KB (small footprint)
- **Dependencies**: 4 packages (express, ws, msgpackr, cors)
- **Features**: PTT audio, video streaming, text chat, file sharing, rooms, authentication

**Complexity**: Moderate - self-contained WebSocket server with clear API

#### Usage Analysis

**Active Usage - 2 Desktop Apps**:

**app-run-observer** (collaborative run viewing):
```javascript
// packages/app-run-observer/dist/index.html:372
const { ZellousSDK } = await import('@sequential/zellous-client-sdk');
zellous = new ZellousSDK({ serverUrl: wsUrl });
// Features: Shows visual badges when collaborators view runs
```

**app-file-browser** (collaborative file browsing):
```javascript
// packages/app-file-browser/dist/index.html:270
const { ZellousSDK } = await import('@sequential/zellous-client-sdk');
zellous = new ZellousSDK({ serverUrl: wsUrl });
// Features: Displays collaborator count banner in directories
```

**Manifest Declarations** (6 apps claim zellous capability):
- app-code-editor
- app-flow-editor
- app-run-observer ✅ (actively uses)
- app-tool-editor
- app-task-editor
- app-file-browser ✅ (actively uses)

**CLI Integration**:
```javascript
// cli.js:188
.option('--no-zellous', 'Start without Zellous')
// Allows disabling zellous server when starting GUI
```

**npm Script**:
```json
// package.json:15
"zellous": "node packages/zellous/server.js"
```

#### Git Activity

**Active Maintenance**:
- **Last 2 months**: 3 commits
- **Last commit**: Dec 1, 2025 - "chore: Update submodule references (Phase 4 complete)"
- **Nature**: Integration commits with sequential-ecosystem

**Recent History**:
```
e2397ef - chore: Update submodule references (Phase 4 complete)
b76e6c8 - Complete real-time integration with zellous and OS.js
994dce4 - Add zellous provider and TaskVFS adapter for real-time collaboration
```

#### Core vs Optional Status

**OPTIONAL Enhancement**:
- ✅ GUI works without zellous (--no-zellous flag)
- ✅ Apps gracefully degrade when SDK import fails
- ✅ Only 2/10 desktop apps actively use it (20% adoption)
- ✅ All 10 apps tested functional without zellous (Nov 30, 2025 testing)

**Not Core Infrastructure**:
- NOT required for task execution
- NOT used by sequential-fetch, sequential-flow, sequential-runner
- NOT part of storage layer or adapters
- Collaboration is enhancement, not core feature

#### Decision Matrix

| Factor | Assessment | Weight | Score |
|--------|-----------|--------|-------|
| **Active Usage** | 2 apps use SDK actively | HIGH | 6/10 |
| **Size Impact** | 23MB reasonable | MEDIUM | 7/10 |
| **Maintenance** | Active integration | HIGH | 8/10 |
| **Value Add** | Collaboration features | MEDIUM | 7/10 |
| **Dependencies** | 4 packages, lightweight | HIGH | 8/10 |
| **Documentation** | Has comprehensive CLAUDE.md | MEDIUM | 9/10 |
| **Git Activity** | Active commits | HIGH | 7/10 |
| **Integration Quality** | Graceful degradation | HIGH | 9/10 |
| **OVERALL** | - | - | **7.6/10** |

**RECOMMENDATION**: ✅ **KEEP but DOCUMENT as OPTIONAL**

#### Implementation Plan: KEEP zellous (Document as Optional)

**Rationale**:
1. **Active Usage**: 2 apps use it for collaboration features
2. **Small Footprint**: 23MB + 40KB (reasonable)
3. **Graceful Degradation**: Apps work without it
4. **Quality Integration**: CLI flag, proper error handling
5. **Future Value**: More apps may adopt collaborative features

**Steps** (20 minutes):

**1. Update CLAUDE.md** (15 min):
```markdown
## Zellous - Real-Time Collaboration (Optional)

**Status**: Optional enhancement - apps gracefully degrade without it
**Usage**: 2/10 desktop apps actively use (app-run-observer, app-file-browser)
**Purpose**: WebRTC-based real-time collaboration with presence, chat, file sharing

### Starting Desktop with Zellous
```bash
npx sequential-ecosystem gui             # With zellous (default)
npx sequential-ecosystem gui --no-zellous  # Without zellous
```

### Package Structure
- **zellous** (23MB): WebSocket server with collaboration features
- **@sequential/zellous-client-sdk** (40KB): Browser SDK for apps

### Active Features
- **app-run-observer**: Shows collaborator badges when viewing runs
- **app-file-browser**: Displays collaborator count in directories

### Adding Zellous to Your App
```javascript
try {
  const { ZellousSDK } = await import('@sequential/zellous-client-sdk');
  const zellous = new ZellousSDK({ serverUrl: 'ws://localhost:3000' });
  await zellous.connect();
  // Use collaboration features
} catch (err) {
  console.log('Zellous not available, continuing without collaboration');
  // App continues without collaboration
}
```

### Documentation
- Full API reference: `packages/zellous/CLAUDE.md`
- Protocol spec: WebSocket message types, REST endpoints
- Features: PTT audio, video, chat, file sharing, rooms, authentication
```

**2. Update Desktop App Manifests** (5 min):
```json
// For apps with zellous capability but not using it:
{
  "capabilities": ["sequential-os"],
  "optionalCapabilities": ["zellous"]
}
```

**3. Add Test Coverage** (deferred):
- Verify graceful degradation in all 6 apps claiming zellous
- Test --no-zellous flag behavior
- Ensure no crashes when SDK unavailable

**Impact**:
- ✅ **Clarity**: Documented as optional enhancement
- ✅ **Flexibility**: Users can disable if not needed
- ✅ **Future-proof**: Foundation for more collaborative features
- ✅ **No Breaking Changes**: All apps already handle graceful degradation

**Risks**: None - already optional in practice

