- **Found In**: 2 packages with overlapping patterns
  - `/packages/response-formatting/src/formatters.js` (100 lines, 11 functions)
  - `/packages/core/src/modules/response/index.js` (86 lines, 6 functions)
- **Overlap**:
  - `formatResponse()` vs `createSuccessResponse()` (same logic)
  - `formatList()` vs `createListResponse()` (same logic)
  - `formatError()` vs `createErrorResponse()` (same logic)
  - `formatPaginated()` vs `createPaginatedResponse()` (same logic)
- **Lines Duplicated**: ~85 lines (similar implementations)
- **Consolidation Effort**: MEDIUM (1-2 hours)
- **Recommendation**: Choose ONE canonical package
  - **Option A**: Keep `@sequential/response-formatting` (more complete, 11 functions)
  - **Option B**: Keep `@sequential/core` response module (more integrated)
  - **Preferred**: Option A (response-formatting is more feature-complete)
- **Impact**: -85 lines saved, clearer API surface

**2.2 File I/O Operations** [CONSOLIDATION OPPORTUNITY]
- **Found In**: 3 packages with similar patterns
  - `/packages/file-operations/src/file-store.js` (68 lines, FileStore class)
  - `/packages/data-access-layer/src/repositories/base-repository.js` (215 lines, includes file I/O)
